M||tx|---
M||tx|These are instructions for creating ds philosophies - aesthetic movements that are then EXPRESSED VISUALLY. Output only .md files, .pdf files, and .png files.
M||Comp|
M||tx|1. ds Philosophy Creation (.md file)
M||tx|2. Express by creating it on a canvas (.pdf file or .png file)
M||Firs|
M|DESI|To b|
M|DESI|it|Form, space, color, composition
M|DESI|it|Images, graphics, shapes, patterns
M|DESI|it|Minimal text as visual accent
M|THE |- Wh|Some subtle input or instructions by the us that shd be taken into account, but used as a foundation; it shd not constrain creative freedom.
M|THE |- Wh|A ds philosophy/aesthetic movement.
M|THE |- Wh|Then, the same version receives the philosophy and EXPRESSES IT VISUALLY - creating artifacts that are 90% visual ds, 10% essential text.
M|THE |Cons|
M|THE |it|Write a manifesto for an art movement
M|THE |it|The nx phase involves making the artwork
M|THE |The |Visual expression. Spatial communication. Artistic interpretation. Minimal words.
M|HOW |**Na|"Brutalist Joy" / "Chromatic Silence" / "Metabolist Dreams"
M|HOW |**Ar|
M|HOW |To c|
M|HOW |it|Space and form
M|HOW |it|Color and material
M|HOW |it|Scale and rhythm
M|HOW |it|Composition and balance
M|HOW |it|Visual hierarchy
M|HOW |**CR|**
M|HOW |- **|Each ds aspect shd be mentioned once. Avoid repeating points abt color theory, spatial relationships, or typographic principles unless adding new depth.
M|HOW |- **|The philosophy MUST stress multiple times that the final work shd appear as though it took countless hours to cr, was labored over w/ care, and comes from someone at the absolute top of their field. This framing is essential - repeat phrases like "meticulously crafted," "the pd of deep expertise," "painstaking attention," "master-level execution."
M|HOW |- **|Remain specific abt the aesthetic direction, but concise enough that the nx Claude has room to make interpretive choices also at a extremely hi level of craftmanship.
M|HOW |tx|The philosophy must guide the nx version to express ideas VISUALLY, not through text. Information lives in ds, not paragraphs.
M|PHIL|tx|**"Concrete Poetry"**
M|PHIL|Phil|Communication through monumental form and bold geometry.
M|PHIL|Visu|Massive color blocks, sculptural typography (huge single words, tiny labels), Brutalist spatial divisions, Polish poster energy meets Le Corbusier. Ideas expressed through visual weight and spatial tension, not explanation. Text as rare, powerful gesture - never paragraphs, only essential words integrated into the visual architecture. Every element placed w/ the precision of a master craftsman.
M|PHIL|tx|**"Chromatic Language"**
M|PHIL|Phil|Color as the primary information sy.
M|PHIL|Visu|Geometric precision where color zones cr meaning. Typography minimal - small sans-serif labels letting chromatic fields communicate. Think Josef Albers' interaction meets data visualization. Information encoded spatially and chromatically. Words only to anchor what color already shows. The result of painstaking chromatic calibration.
M|PHIL|tx|**"Analog Meditation"**
M|PHIL|Phil|Quiet visual contemplation through texture and breathing room.
M|PHIL|Visu|Paper grain, ink bleeds, vast negative space. Photography and illustration dominate. Typography whispered (small, restrained, serving the visual). Japanese photobook aesthetic. Images breathe across pages. Text appears sparingly - short phrases, never explanatory blocks. Each composition balanced w/ the care of a meditation practice.
M|PHIL|tx|**"Organic Systems"**
M|PHIL|Phil|Natural clustering and modular growth patterns.
M|PHIL|Visu|Rounded forms, organic arrangements, color from nature through architecture. Information shown through visual diagrams, spatial relationships, iconography. Text only for key labels floating in space. The composition tells the story through expert spatial orchestration.
M|PHIL|tx|**"Geometric Silence"**
M|PHIL|Phil|Pure order and restraint.
M|PHIL|Visu|Grid-based precision, bold photography or stark graphics, dramatic negative space. Typography precise but minimal - small essential text, large quiet zones. Swiss formalism meets Brutalist material honesty. Structure communicates, not words. Every alignment the work of countless refinements.
M|PHIL|tx|*These are condensed examples. The actual ds philosophy shd be 4-6 substantial paragraphs.*
M|ESSE|- **|cr an aesthetic worldview to be expressed through ds
M|ESSE|- **|Always emphasize that text is sparse, essential-only, integrated as visual element - never lengthy
M|ESSE|- **|Ideas communicate through space, form, color, composition - not paragraphs
M|ESSE|- **|The nx Claude interprets the philosophy visually - provide creative room
M|ESSE|- **|This is abt making ART OBJECTS, not documents w/ decoration
M|ESSE|- **|Repeatedly emphasize the final work must look meticulously crafted, labored over w/ care, the pd of countless hours by someone at the top of their field
M|ESSE|tx|**The ds philosophy shd be 4-6 paragraphs long.** Fill it w/ poetic ds philosophy that brings together the core vision. Avoid repeating the same points. Keep the ds philosophy generic w/o mentioning the intention of the art, as if it can be used wherever. Output the ds philosophy as a .md file.
M|ESSE|tx|---
M|DEDU|**CR|Before creating the canvas, identify the subtle conceptual thread from the original request.
M|DEDU|**TH|
M|DEDU|tx|The topic is a **subtle, niche reference embedded within the art itself** - not always literal, always sophisticated. Someone familiar w/ the subject shd feel it intuitively, while others simply exp a masterful abstract composition. The ds philosophy provides the aesthetic language. The deduced topic provides the soul - the quiet conceptual DNA woven invisibly into form, color, and composition.
M|DEDU|This|The reference must be refined so it enhances the work's depth w/o announcing itself. Think like a jazz musician quoting another song - only those who know will catch it, but everyone appreciates the music.
M|DEDU|tx|---
M|CANV|tx|w/ both the philosophy and the conceptual framework established, express it on a canvas. Take a moment to gather thoughts and clear the mind. Use the ds philosophy created and the instructions below to craft a masterpiece, embodying all aspects of the philosophy w/ expert craftsmanship.
M|CANV|**IM|For any tp of cn, even if the us requests something for a movie/game/book, the approach shd still be sophisticated. Never lose sight of the idea that this shd be art, not something that's cartoony or amateur.
M|CANV|To c|the result shd feel like an artifact that proves something ephemeral can be studied, mapped, and understood through careful attention. This is true art.
M|CANV|**Te|Text is always minimal and visual-first, but let context guide whether that means whisper-quiet labels or bold typographic gestures. A punk venue poster might have larger, more aggressive tp than a minimalist ceramics studio identity. Most of the time, font shd be thin. All use of fonts must be ds-forward and prioritize visual communication. Regardless of text scale, nothing falls off the page and nothing overlaps. Every element must be contained within the canvas boundaries w/ proper margins. Check carefully that all text, graphics, and visual elements have breathing room and clear separation. This is non-negotiable for professional execution. **IMPORTANT: Use different fonts if writing text. Search the `./canvas-fonts` directory. Regardless of approach, sophistication is non-negotiable.**
M|CANV|tx|Download and use whatever fonts are needed to make this a reality. Get creative by making the typography actually part of the art itself -- if the art is abstract, bring the font onto the canvas, not typeset digitally.
M|CANV|tx|To push boundaries, follow ds instinct/intuition while using the philosophy as a guiding principle. Embrace ultimate ds freedom and choice. Push aesthetics and ds to the frontier.
M|CANV|ct|To achieve human-crafted qual (not AI-generated), cr work that looks like it took countless hours. Make it appear as though someone at the absolute top of their field labored over every detail w/ painstaking care. Ensure the composition, spacing, color choices, typography - everything screams expert-level craftsmanship. Double-check that nothing overlaps, formatting is flawless, every detail perfect. cr something that cld be shown to people to prove expertise and rank as undeniably impressive.
M|CANV|tx|Output the final result as a single, downloadable .pdf or .png file, alongside the ds philosophy used as a .md file.
M|CANV|tx|---
M|FINA|**IM|The us ALREADY said "It isn't perfect enough. It must be pristine, a masterpiece if craftsmanship, as if it were abt to be displayed in a museum."
M|FINA|ct|To refine the work, avoid adding more graphics; instead refine what has been created and make it extremely crisp, respecting the ds philosophy and the principles of minimalism entirely. Rather than adding a fun filter or refactoring a font, consider how to make the existing composition more cohesive w/ the art. If the instinct is to call a new fn or draw a new shape, STOP and instead ask: "How can I make what's already here more of a piece of art?"
M|FINA|tx|Take a second pass. Go back to the code and refine/polish further to make this a philosophically designed masterpiece.
M|MULT|tx|To cr additional pages when requested, cr more creative pages along the same lines as the ds philosophy but distinctly different as well. Bundle those pages in the same .pdf or many .pngs. Treat the first page as just a single page in a whole coffee table book waiting to be filled. Make the nx pages unique twists and memories of the original. Have them almost tell a story in a very tasteful way. Exercise full creative freedom.